{"title_page": "Season of the Devil", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Season of the Devil\n| film name      = {{infobox name module|language=tl|title=Ang Panahon ng Halimaw|nolink=1}}\n| image          = Season of the Devil.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Lav Diaz]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Bianca Balbuena\n* Lav Diaz\n* Quark Henares\n* Bradley Liew\n}}\n| writer         = Lav Diaz\n| starring       = [[Piolo Pascual]]\n| music          = Lav Diaz\n| cinematography = Larry Manda\n| editing        = Lav Diaz\n| studio         = {{ubl|Epicmedia|Sine Olivia Pilipinas}}\n| released       = {{film date|2018|2|20|[[68th Berlin International Film Festival|Berlinale]]|2018|5|28|Philippines|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 234 minutes\n| country        = Philippines\n| language       = Filipino\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Season of the Devil''''' ({{lang-fil|'''Ang Panahon ng Halimaw''')<ref name=\"Berlin\">{{cite web|url=https://www.berlinale.de/en/presse/pressemitteilungen/alle/Alle-Detail_41364.html |title=Press Releases: 68th Berlinale |date=22 January 2018|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref>}} is a 2018 Filipino [[musical film]] directed by [[Lav Diaz]]. It was selected to compete for the [[Golden Bear]] in the main competition section at the [[68th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/global/berlin-film-festival-robert-pattinson-1202664442/ |title=Berlin Film Festival Fleshes Out Competition Lineup |work=Variety |date=15 January 2018 |accessdate=17 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Berlin\"/> The film has a running time of 234 minutes.<ref name=\"Lodge 2018\">{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/reviews/season-of-the-devil-review-berlinale-2018-1202704763/|title=Berlin Film Review: \u2018Season of the Devil\u2019|last=Lodge|first=Guy|date=21 February 2018|work=Variety|access-date=12 April 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nLorena (Shaina Magdayao) is a young doctor who opens a clinic for the poor in a remote Philippine village in the late 1970s. The village is controlled and terrorized by uniformed armed men, which the prologue of the film identifies as members of the Martial Law era [[Civilian Home Defense Forces]]<ref name=\"Guerrero 2018\" /> \n\nLorena disappears without a trace, prompting her husband Hugo (Piolo Pascual), an activist, poet, and teacher, to come looking for her. Hugo comes to the village and comes face to face with a community \"shattered by despotism and violence.\"<ref name=\"Guerrero 2018\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/movies/27754/lav-diaz-why-do-we-still-have-guys-like-duterte-trump-and-all-those-motherfrs|title=Lav Diaz rants against \"Duterte, Trump...motherf****rs\"|last=Guerrero|first=Kaye|date=11 April 2018|work=PEP|access-date=12 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n\n===Main cast===\n* [[Piolo Pascual]] as Hugo Haniway\n* [[Shaina Magdayao]] as Lorena Haniway\n\n===Supporting cast===\n* [[Angel Aquino]] as Anghelita\n* [[Pinky Amador]] as Kwago\n* [[Bituin Escalante]] as Kwentista\n* [[Hazel Orencio]] as Teniente \n* Bart Guingona as Paham\n* Joel Saracho as Ahas\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical reception===\nOn [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has an approval rating of 100% based on 6 reviews, and an [[average rating]] of 7.5/10.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/season_of_the_devil |title=''Season of the Devil'' (''Ang Panahon ng Halimaw'') (2018) |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |accessdate=22 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n''Variety'' praised the director for remaining \"emphatically his own artist, whether to exhilarating or punishing effect,\" saying the movie has some \"raw, stirring interludes.\" It however thought that Diaz's editing weakened the film's impact, saying \"it\u2019s hard not to wonder what finer rhythmic and tonal variations another editor\u2026 might have brought to the table this time.\"<ref name=\"Lodge 2018\" />\n\n''The Hollywood Reporter'' called the film a \"seething critique about the Philippines\u2019 current trigger-happy president in the form of a 'rock opera.'\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/season-devil-ang-panahon-ng-halimaw-film-review-berlin-2018-1086017|title='Season of the Devil' ('Ang Panahon ng Halimaw'): Film Review {{!}} Berlin 2018|last=Tsui|first=Clarence|date=20 February 2018|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=12 April 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n''Season of the Devil'' won best film in the Gems section of 58th Festival Internacional de Cine Cartagena de Indias held in Colombia in March 2018.<ref name=\"Guerrero 2018\" />\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of films about martial law in the Philippines]]\n* [[Civilian Home Defense Forces]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|7200370|Season of the Devil}}\n\n{{Lav Diaz}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Season Of The Devil}}\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical films]]\n[[Category:Philippine films]]\n[[Category:Philippine musical films]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Lav Diaz]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Season of the Devil\n| film name      = {{infobox name module|language=tl|title=Ang Panahon ng Halimaw|nolink=1}}\n| image          = Season of the Devil.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Lav Diaz]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Bianca Balbuena\n* Lav Diaz\n* Quark Henares\n* Bradley Liew\n}}\n| writer         = Lav Diaz\n| starring       = [[Piolo Pascual]]\n| music          = Lav Diaz\n| cinematography = Larry Manda\n| editing        = Lav Diaz\n| studio         = {{ubl|Epicmedia|Sine Olivia Pilipinas}}\n| released       = {{film date|2018|2|20|[[68th Berlin International Film Festival|Berlinale]]|2018|5|28|Philippines|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 234 minutes\n| country        = Philippines\n| language       = Filipino\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Season of the Devil''''' ({{lang-fil|'''Ang Panahon ng Halimaw''')<ref name=\"Berlin\">{{cite web|url=https://www.berlinale.de/en/presse/pressemitteilungen/alle/Alle-Detail_41364.html |title=Press Releases: 68th Berlinale |date=22 January 2018|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref>}} is a 2018 Filipino [[musical film]] directed by [[Lav Diaz]]. It was selected to compete for the [[Golden Bear]] in the main competition section at the [[68th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/global/berlin-film-festival-robert-pattinson-1202664442/ |title=Berlin Film Festival Fleshes Out Competition Lineup |work=Variety |date=15 January 2018 |accessdate=17 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Berlin\"/> The film has a running time of 234 minutes.<ref name=\"Lodge 2018\">{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/reviews/season-of-the-devil-review-berlinale-2018-1202704763/|title=Berlin Film Review: \u2018Season of the Devil\u2019|last=Lodge|first=Guy|date=21 February 2018|work=Variety|access-date=12 April 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nLorena (Shaina Magdayao) is a young doctor who opens a clinic for the poor in a remote Philippine village in the late 1970s. The village is controlled and terrorized by uniformed armed men, which the prologue of the film identifies as members of the Martial Law era [[Civilian Home Defense Forces]]<ref name=\"Guerrero 2018\" /> \n\nLorena disappears without a trace, prompting her husband Hugo (Piolo Pascual), an activist, poet, and teacher, to come looking for her. Hugo comes to the village and comes face to face with a community \"shattered by despotism and violence.\"<ref name=\"Guerrero 2018\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/movies/27754/lav-diaz-why-do-we-still-have-guys-like-duterte-trump-and-all-those-motherfrs|title=Lav Diaz rants against \"Duterte, Trump...motherf****rs\"|last=Guerrero|first=Kaye|date=11 April 2018|work=PEP|access-date=12 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n\n===Main cast===\n* [[Piolo Pascual]] as Hugo Haniway\n* [[Shaina Magdayao]] as Lorena Haniway\n\n===Supporting cast===\n* [[Angel Aquino]] as Anghelita\n* [[Pinky Amador]] as Kwago\n* [[Bituin Escalante]] as Kwentista\n* [[Hazel Orencio]] as Teniente \n* Bart Guingona as Paham\n* Joel Saracho as Ahas\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical reception===\nOn [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has an approval rating of 100% based on 6 reviews, and an [[average rating]] of 7.5/10.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/season_of_the_devil |title=''Season of the Devil'' (''Ang Panahon ng Halimaw'') (2018) |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |publisher=[[Fandango Media]] |accessdate=22 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n''Variety'' praised the director for remaining \"emphatically his own artist, whether to exhilarating or punishing effect,\" saying the movie has some \"raw, stirring interludes.\" It however thought that Diaz's editing weakened the film's impact, saying \"it\u2019s hard not to wonder what finer rhythmic and tonal variations another editor\u2026 might have brought to the table this time.\"<ref name=\"Lodge 2018\" />\n\n''The Hollywood Reporter'' called the film a \"seething critique about the Philippines\u2019 current trigger-happy president in the form of a 'rock opera.'\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/season-devil-ang-panahon-ng-halimaw-film-review-berlin-2018-1086017|title='Season of the Devil' ('Ang Panahon ng Halimaw'): Film Review {{!}} Berlin 2018|last=Tsui|first=Clarence|date=20 February 2018|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=12 April 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n''Season of the Devil'' won best film in the Gems section of 58th Festival Internacional de Cine Cartagena de Indias held in Colombia in March 2018.<ref name=\"Guerrero 2018\" />\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of films about martial law in the Philippines]]\n* [[Civilian Home Defense Forces]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|7200370|Season of the Devil}}\n\n{{Lav Diaz}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Season Of The Devil}}\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical films]]\n[[Category:Philippine films]]\n[[Category:Philippine musical films]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Lav Diaz]]\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Season_of_the_Devil"}
